readme.md
    20Рєњ## Benefits over plain `fetch`
    22Рєњ- Simpler API
    23Рєњ- Method shortcuts (`ky.post()`)
    24Рєњ- Treats non-2xx status codes as errors (after redirects)
    25Рєњ- Retries failed requests
    26Рєњ- JSON option
    27Рєњ- Timeout support
    28Рєњ- URL prefix option
    29Рєњ- Instances with custom defaults
    30Рєњ- Hooks
    31Рєњ- TypeScript niceties (e.g. `.json()` supports generics and defaults to `unknown`, not `any`)
    32Рєњ
    33Рєњ## Install
    35Рєњ```sh
    36Рєњnpm install ky
    37Рєњ```
    38Рєњ
    45Рєњ## Usage
    47Рєњ```js
    48Рєњimport ky from 'ky';
    49Рєњ
    50Рєњconst json = await ky.post('https://example.com', {json: {foo: true}}).json();
    51Рєњ
    52Рєњconsole.log(json);
    53Рєњ//=> {data: '­Ъдё'}
    54Рєњ```
    55Рєњ
    56РєњWith plain `fetch`, it would be:
    57Рєњ
    58Рєњ```js
    59Рєњclass HTTPError extends Error {}
    60Рєњ
    61Рєњconst response = await fetch('https://example.com', {
    62Рєњ	method: 'POST',
      Рєњ	Рђд
